04:02.434 --> 04:06.320
Yeah, yeah, yeah!

04:06.340 --> 04:10.107
How many came for a word from God today?

04:10.728 --> 04:18.080
Make some noise!

04:18.821 --> 04:22.747
I want to draw your attention while you're standing to John chapter 9, please.

04:24.150 --> 04:25.352
I've got a brand new Bible.

04:25.712 --> 04:29.138
Junks and Amy gave me a brand new Bible for our 20th birthday.

04:29.730 --> 04:32.353
So let's take it for a spin and see how it preaches.

04:33.455 --> 04:34.316
I was insulted.

04:34.336 --> 04:35.978
They gave me a large print Bible.

04:36.038 --> 04:37.700
I'm like, what is that supposed to mean?

04:41.785 --> 04:47.011
So since it was a large print Bible, I thought I'd preach about the blind man in John chapter nine.

04:51.396 --> 04:52.818
I'm so thankful that you're here.

04:58.914 --> 05:04.802
John chapter nine is a great chapter and you may do well to read the whole thing when you get home.

05:04.882 --> 05:06.804
I'm gonna deal with the first half of this story.

05:07.906 --> 05:09.348
The scriptures are coming on the screen.

05:10.990 --> 05:16.257
As he went along, he saw a man, Jesus saw a man, blind from birth.

05:17.318 --> 05:18.660
Now, can we preach a whole message about that?

05:19.160 --> 05:21.704
As he went along, he saw a man, blind from birth.

05:22.885 --> 05:26.610
The man didn't see Jesus, but Jesus saw the man.

05:28.162 --> 05:34.572
Yeah, we could preach a whole sermon on that, about how when you weren't even looking for him, he found you.

05:37.696 --> 05:43.285
His disciples, verse two, asked him, Rabbi, who send this man or his parents that he was born blind?

05:44.667 --> 05:45.007
Neither.

05:46.229 --> 05:48.573
Neither.

05:50.255 --> 05:54.902
Jesus sums up an entire theological library in one word.

05:55.223 --> 05:57.426
Neither.

05:57.570 --> 05:58.872
Both options are stupid.

05:59.212 --> 06:03.078
Neither this man nor his parents sinned, said Jesus.

06:03.798 --> 06:06.903
But this happened so that the works of God might be displayed in him.

06:07.744 --> 06:11.229
As long as it is day, we must do the works of him who sent me.

06:11.950 --> 06:15.534
Night is coming when no one can work while I'm in the world.

06:16.215 --> 06:17.938
I am the light of the world.

06:18.799 --> 06:24.927
After saying this, he spit on the ground, made some mud with the saliva and put it on the man's eyes.

06:25.808 --> 06:26.930
Go, he told him.

06:27.330 --> 06:29.972
Wash in the pool of Siloam.

06:30.013 --> 06:31.574
This word means sent.

06:32.475 --> 06:36.419
So the man went and washed and came home seeing.

06:37.279 --> 06:37.820
Oh, that's good.

06:38.160 --> 06:40.943
He went and washed and came home seeing.

06:41.383 --> 06:51.673
His neighbors and those who had formerly seen him begging asked, isn't this the same man who used to sit and beg some claim that he was?

06:52.294 --> 06:54.656
Others said, no, he only looks like him.

06:55.196 --> 06:56.978
But he himself insisted.

06:57.282 --> 06:57.903
I'm the man.

06:59.805 --> 07:01.687
It's me."

07:01.707 --> 07:03.590
How then were your eyes opened, they asked.

07:03.630 --> 07:11.319
He replied, the man they call Jesus made some mud and put it on my eyes.

07:12.420 --> 07:12.921
Yeah, I know.

07:13.041 --> 07:13.742
It wasn't pretty.

07:14.783 --> 07:15.124
I know.

07:15.724 --> 07:17.526
I didn't see it coming, literally.

07:18.568 --> 07:25.296
He made some mud and put it on my eyes, and he told me to go to Siloam and wash.

07:26.117 --> 07:27.058
So I went.

07:27.778 --> 07:31.944
and washed and then I could see.

07:31.984 --> 07:37.692
I want to talk to you today about when waiting isn't working.

07:40.396 --> 07:42.619
When waiting isn't working.

07:43.580 --> 07:46.464
Put that in the chat please or the comments if you're watching later.

07:46.885 --> 07:51.311
When waiting isn't working.

07:51.592 --> 07:52.373
Not getting better.

07:53.555 --> 07:54.676
Not healing the wound.

07:54.856 --> 07:56.018
When waiting

07:56.674 --> 07:57.415
isn't working.

07:57.495 --> 07:58.476
Nothing's changing.

07:59.517 --> 08:00.518
No doors are opening.

08:00.538 --> 08:01.700
I want to talk about that today.

08:01.980 --> 08:04.162
When waiting isn't working.

08:05.003 --> 08:06.825
And I gave the message of subtitle too.

08:07.546 --> 08:10.369
The subtitle is muddy moves.

08:12.271 --> 08:13.913
Muddy moves.

08:14.033 --> 08:16.115
Tell somebody I make muddy moves.

08:17.537 --> 08:17.837
Yeah.

08:17.917 --> 08:18.938
Father bless your word.

08:19.479 --> 08:20.240
In Jesus name.

08:20.881 --> 08:21.201
Amen.

08:21.241 --> 08:22.162
You may be seated.

08:39.682 --> 08:40.623
How long would you sit there?

08:44.409 --> 08:47.554
If I just came up here, made you wait.

08:53.102 --> 08:57.588
Now we need to have an altar call for lying, for all of you who sit all day.

08:57.608 --> 09:06.802
I mean, they don't even stay till I do my invitation half the time, tripping over people in the back of the parking lot all day.

09:09.346 --> 09:10.988
No, really, how long would you sit there?

09:12.671 --> 09:15.295
You know, waiting, waiting.

09:15.315 --> 09:16.637
Sometimes it's worth the wait.

09:18.219 --> 09:18.980
Sometimes it's not.

09:21.303 --> 09:27.773
When I first met Holly, she was on a dating probation, a probationary period.

09:28.794 --> 09:36.946
And the thing was, she just wanted to take some time to really be anchored in her values when she went to college before

09:37.570 --> 09:41.676
she got entangled with somebody who may or may not share those values, right?

09:43.078 --> 09:48.767
And I think that's great because I can attest to the fact that she is absolutely worth the wait.

09:50.389 --> 09:56.358
But I was in line and I cut in line and I put her on my ministry team.

09:57.219 --> 10:04.971
So whenever the Lord spoke to her that the probation had been lifted and the wait is over, I wanted to be the one.

10:05.011 --> 10:07.154
Yeah.

10:08.162 --> 10:12.828
And here we are, 27 years of being Valentine's.

10:12.848 --> 10:15.051
27 years.

10:15.952 --> 10:18.856
You learn a lot about love in 27 years.

10:18.896 --> 10:20.758
You learn a lot about Valentine's Day.

10:21.039 --> 10:33.635
You learn to go out two days before Valentine's Day to the restaurant and be at the restaurant when they're not overbooking the place, putting you a little table somewhere in the bathroom and charging you full price on Valentine's Day.

10:33.895 --> 10:36.018
We go out on February 12th.

10:36.290 --> 10:44.918
And yet what amazes me is that as long as this woman has known me, there are certain things that she still does not understand about the difference in our dynamic.

10:45.319 --> 10:55.349
So when we were going out on our Valentine's Day date, two days early, a few days ago, I came upstairs after my workout and I'm sweating and I'm not ready.

10:55.869 --> 10:59.212
And we have to leave for the reservation in just a few minutes.

10:59.793 --> 11:01.214
And she's finishing getting ready.

11:01.555 --> 11:05.138
And she looks at me and it's like, you know, nicely, she's trying to do a nice thing.

11:05.250 --> 11:06.512
Do you want me to push the reservation back?

11:07.934 --> 11:09.977
And I'm like, you don't need to push the reservation back.

11:11.199 --> 11:20.293
How do you not know after all these years of being married to me that it doesn't take me long?

11:22.597 --> 11:24.339
I mean, Holly, I love you.

11:24.359 --> 11:25.121
Thank you for asking.

11:25.161 --> 11:33.874
But we both know that you finishing getting ready and me getting ready all the way from

11:34.434 --> 11:37.138
the starting point of readiness in the beginning.

11:37.178 --> 11:47.233
Like, I can take a shower, get dressed, write a song, support a missionary.

11:49.977 --> 11:53.322
In the time you can put on this lip gloss.

11:53.342 --> 11:56.947
I don't know how that works out, but it doesn't take me long.

11:57.989 --> 12:00.593
When I get ready, I do it quick.

12:01.834 --> 12:04.338
It amazes me in the Scripture

12:05.218 --> 12:08.722
how much Jesus did with so little time on earth.

12:10.264 --> 12:21.696
You hear in John chapter nine, he makes a statement, as long as I am in the world, I'm the light of the world, but I've got to do the work that God called me to do in the window that God gave me to do it.

12:22.617 --> 12:24.219
And that might be a word for you too.

12:25.000 --> 12:30.866
I've got to do the work that God called me to do in the window that God gave me to do it.

12:31.618 --> 12:38.746
and that will help you put off procrastination and that'll help you sometimes stop thinking that you've always got more time than you really do.

12:39.327 --> 12:50.180
But when Jesus said, I must work the works of him who sent me while it's day, I think he was also reminding his disciples, it doesn't take me long.

12:50.941 --> 12:57.248
And I wanna remind somebody today, and maybe this will be the whole reason you came for the message, that it doesn't take God long.

12:58.549 --> 12:59.090
It doesn't.

13:00.194 --> 13:06.140
the one who created the world in six days and said, well, we could chill on the seventh because I'm done.

13:06.180 --> 13:09.543
It doesn't take God long to work.

13:09.563 --> 13:11.585
It doesn't take God long to work.

13:12.025 --> 13:20.513
The one who can make the walls fall, a project that would have taken a demolition crew, perhaps weeks of permitting alone and he can do it with the blow of a trumpet.

13:20.773 --> 13:22.715
It doesn't take God long.

13:23.716 --> 13:26.098
God chooses when he wants to move.

13:26.839 --> 13:29.842
But when he moves, it doesn't take him long.

13:30.306 --> 13:40.425
So don't be discouraged if you think it's taking too long because God can do something in a moment that will make up for a month of what you thought was wasted time.

13:40.966 --> 13:43.551
It doesn't take God long.

13:44.172 --> 13:46.637
Reach around and tell three people it doesn't take him long.

13:48.220 --> 13:49.362
It doesn't take him long.

13:49.666 --> 13:50.947
That's what I was telling Holly.

13:51.187 --> 13:52.448
Go ahead and finish doing it.

13:52.468 --> 14:03.038
By the time you get done curling your eyelashes, I will be in the Jeep waiting for you impatiently, because it doesn't take me as long as it takes you.

14:03.058 --> 14:06.681
And so God wants you to know, I know you feel behind.

14:07.081 --> 14:08.522
I know it feels like forever.

14:08.602 --> 14:09.483
Who am I preaching to?

14:09.803 --> 14:11.185
But this is the word of the Lord.

14:11.505 --> 14:17.410
When he gets ready to do what he's going to do, it will not take him long to do it.

14:17.911 --> 14:19.652
God can turn things around so

14:19.632 --> 14:22.776
God can turn things around so completely.

14:23.196 --> 14:30.846
God can do a reversal so suddenly that the last will be first and the first will be last.

14:31.306 --> 14:34.590
God can move you right to the front of the cafeteria line.

14:35.111 --> 14:40.577
God can put you right in the door that many people shut on you and God kicks it open.

14:40.958 --> 14:44.282
And when God kicks it open, back up everybody else.

14:44.682 --> 14:47.826
It doesn't take God long.

14:50.114 --> 14:54.862
Now, Jesus said, I've got to do the work of him who sent me while it's day.

14:55.202 --> 15:07.842
And for those of you who think that I'm just up here trying to give people encouragement for, you know, sudden breakthroughs and aha moments and, you know, complete reversals overnight, I am not that kind of preacher.

15:08.824 --> 15:14.493
If you've experienced my ministry for any length of time, I am a process oriented preacher.

15:15.955 --> 15:17.938
And so one time, early in,

15:18.242 --> 15:25.535
My ministry, I was experiencing this differential between patience and passive.

15:27.578 --> 15:34.671
I sat down to explain to our team how we were gonna go to two services because we were full in our first service.

15:35.492 --> 15:43.186
And the whole team started arguing about whether or not we should go to two services, not two campuses, two services.

15:43.906 --> 15:48.231
And some thought it would be too taxing and some thought it would be too consuming and some thought it would be too much.

15:49.433 --> 15:54.178
As a matter of fact, I even had a meeting with another person to ask about, should we go to two services?

15:55.059 --> 15:58.163
And the person said back to me, well, maybe you should wait on God.

15:59.745 --> 16:01.607
And then he said something real profound, write this down.

16:02.368 --> 16:07.634
The only thing harder than waiting on God is wishing that you had.

16:12.290 --> 16:14.494
Ain't that a whole bird word?

16:16.076 --> 16:38.834
I mean, that is so true that sometimes when we are waiting for God to do something, it feels so hard that the temptation to step outside of God's will and God's way to get it done, the temptation to get us a Hagar since Sarah can't have a baby, the temptation for us to do the sacrifice since the priest aren't coming,

16:39.490 --> 16:44.276
The temptation for us to reach for a bottle because we're sick and tired of waiting for breakthrough.

16:44.676 --> 16:50.323
The temptation to step outside of who you are to get what you want and you need so badly, it can be so great.

16:51.505 --> 17:01.917
But the only thing harder than waiting on God is wishing that you had and waking up to decisions that you made because you didn't wait.

17:03.699 --> 17:09.266
So then the next day I had another meeting with another mentor and I said, Hey,

17:09.506 --> 17:11.349
I've decided not to go to two services.

17:12.651 --> 17:13.913
I don't think I should right now.

17:14.654 --> 17:15.916
I think I should wait on the Lord.

17:15.936 --> 17:16.917
He said, wait on the Lord.

17:17.218 --> 17:17.939
The room is full.

17:19.441 --> 17:19.922
I was there.

17:19.942 --> 17:20.783
I couldn't get a seat.

17:22.666 --> 17:23.607
He said it was terrible.

17:23.647 --> 17:24.809
It was a terrible experience.

17:24.849 --> 17:26.431
I mean, I know it was good for you as a preacher.

17:26.451 --> 17:29.015
It's a full room, but for somebody trying to get a seat, it was a problem.

17:29.877 --> 17:32.320
And then you got up there and told us to invite our friends next week.

17:32.400 --> 17:33.682
Invite them to come to what?

17:34.283 --> 17:34.784
Sit them where?

17:34.864 --> 17:35.285
Put them where?

17:35.325 --> 17:36.146
Where are you going to put them?

17:39.394 --> 17:40.976
I said, but I don't want to get ahead of God.

17:41.036 --> 17:43.698
And he said, well, here's how God works.

17:43.998 --> 17:44.939
Here's how God works.

17:45.740 --> 17:50.965
If you get ahead of God in an effort to obey him, he can close the door and slow you down.

17:52.326 --> 17:57.111
If you get behind God because you won't obey him, he'll choose somebody else to use.

18:00.574 --> 18:01.955
So we went to two services.

18:04.278 --> 18:08.882
Because I realized something about God, I realized something

18:09.090 --> 18:09.932
about waiting.

18:10.132 --> 18:11.915
I realized something about myself.

18:12.296 --> 18:14.841
I realized something about Jesus.

18:15.763 --> 18:16.204
It is this.

18:16.564 --> 18:22.756
Sometimes we think we're waiting when we are really disobeying.

18:25.983 --> 18:26.664
I'm going to say it again.

18:26.684 --> 18:27.505
That's my whole message.

18:29.429 --> 18:31.954
Are you calling it waiting?

18:32.450 --> 18:33.772
when it's really disobeying.

18:33.792 --> 18:35.013
I mean, notice the disciples here.

18:35.053 --> 18:41.841
They see a man who's blind from birth and their first instinct is to ask Jesus a theological question.

18:42.402 --> 18:44.044
You know, whose fault was it?

18:44.424 --> 18:49.730
Was it his fault or was it his parents fault that he was born blind?

18:49.870 --> 18:51.873
Now this man has been born his whole life.

18:51.953 --> 18:56.338
We find out later in John chapter nine that he is of legal age.

18:56.514 --> 19:01.238
He is at least a grown man, and he may be an older grown man.

19:01.619 --> 19:07.044
We do not know his exact age, but we know that he has been in this condition his whole life.

19:07.705 --> 19:16.753
And one encounter with Jesus, it doesn't take God long, opens up his eyes to see a world that he has previously only experienced through other senses.

19:17.574 --> 19:26.162
However, had it been up to Jesus' disciples what happened to this dude, all that would have happened that day was a good debate.

19:27.810 --> 19:33.810
because the disciples saw a debate, but Jesus saw a display.

19:36.037 --> 19:38.706
They said, let's talk about this man's condition.

19:38.818 --> 19:40.960
Let's talk about whose fault it was.

19:41.360 --> 19:43.622
Let's talk about what landed him in this place.

19:44.143 --> 19:48.446
Let's check his internet search history and see if he's looking at the right websites.

19:48.847 --> 19:53.090
Let's check his doctrine and see if he believes in substitutionary atonement.

19:53.471 --> 19:58.655
Let's look and see if he has memorized an adequate number of scriptures to get him healed and stuff.

19:58.975 --> 20:08.804
And Jesus circumventing all of that and Jesus walking by all of that and Jesus ignoring all of that reaches down in the dirt, something that they are

20:08.784 --> 20:13.970
walking on top of and puts it on the eyes of somebody that they are walking past.

20:14.350 --> 20:16.813
They had no intention of stopping for the man.

20:17.194 --> 20:18.675
They just wanted to talk about him.

20:19.076 --> 20:20.998
They had no power to heal the man.

20:21.418 --> 20:23.080
They just wanted to debate about it.

20:23.481 --> 20:25.443
They had no power to do anything about it.

20:25.763 --> 20:35.314
Watch out for people who are always debating and never displaying.

20:36.162 --> 20:48.943
Watch out for people who are always trying to qualify who should and should not be called by God, especially if they are unwilling to go through that same qualification process themselves.

20:50.846 --> 20:54.051
So Jesus says, you see him as a debate.

20:55.012 --> 20:56.375
I see him as a display.

20:57.276 --> 21:00.241
You see him as someone who is crippled by blindness.

21:01.082 --> 21:03.506
I see him as a canvas for glory.

21:04.194 --> 21:07.020
You see him as somebody to walk past.

21:07.641 --> 21:10.086
I see him as somebody to work through.

21:10.787 --> 21:13.072
You see him as a blind man.

21:13.633 --> 21:15.377
I see him as a vessel.

21:15.798 --> 21:17.421
You see his lack of vision.

21:17.441 --> 21:19.224
I see his value.

21:19.926 --> 21:23.954
Because the only one not blind in this passage is Jesus.

21:24.194 --> 21:25.556
The man is blind.

21:25.817 --> 21:27.599
The disciples are blind.

21:27.619 --> 21:29.242
The Pharisees are blind.

